import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of home scores?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Home Scores")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('division')['score_difference'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='division', y='score_difference', data=data_grouped)
    plt.title('What is the average score difference by division?', wrap=True)
    chart.set(xlabel='Division', ylabel='Average Score Difference')
    plt.legend(title='Division', loc='upper right', labels=data_grouped['division'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='home_score', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of home scores over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Home Score')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Home Score'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
